/** \page RELEASENOTES RELEASENOTES
 *
 * v0.2.4	OpenSEK Beta Release 200903xx
 *		- port OpenSEK for ARM Architecture (tested on lpc2468)
 *		- first version of the Dio driver (concept phase) is available
 *		- first version of the Mcu Driver (concept phase) is available
 *		- move the tests to the tst folder
 *		- move the examples to the examples folder
 *		- move the generator from the OpenSEK module to OpenGEN module
 *		- start porting uIP to OpenSEK environment
 *		- add first sturcture of a Memory Mapping concept based on Autosar
 *		- add a Types.h for all generic types definitions
 *		- some bug fixing work
 *		- add licensing exception if OpenSEK is used as library
 *
 * v0.2.3	OpenSEK Beta Release 20081102
 *		- add Manual Structure
 *		- write first OpenSEK OS Manual (not yet complete)
 *		- fix win and posix stack probelm (id: 2166476)
 *		- add requirement tracing documentation
 *		- add RAM/ROM memory consumption documentation
 *
 * v0.2.2	OpenSEK Beta Release 20081012
 * 	- add support for windows (cygwin)
 * 	- generic os file were checked with splint
 * 	- extend the documentation a little bit
 *
 * v0.2.1	OpenSEK Beta Release 20080926
 * 	- add splint checks
 * 	- add requirements tracing on the code
 * 	- avoid reentrance of the error hook
 * 	- add the followings hooks
 * 		- startuphook
 * 		- shutdownhook
 * 	- some order was performed on the c and h files
 * 	- update all disable/enable algorithm, a counter is used insted of stack
 *
 * v0.2.0	OpenSEK Pre Beta Release 2 20080922
 * 	- Complete GetAlarm/SetRelAlarm/SetAbsAlarm/CancelAlarm interfaces
 * 	- Complete Resume/SuspendAllInterrupts interfaces 
 * 	- Complete Enable/DisableAllInterrupts interfaces
 * 	- Complete Resume/SuspendOSInterrupts interfaces
 * 	- Add Counters simulators for posix
 * 	- Complete some testcases
 *
 * v0.1.0	First OpenSEK Pre Beta Release 20080917
 * 	- OpenSEK was only tested with the moduletest01 example.
 * 	- OpenSEK tests are not complet.
 * 	- The following apis are not finished:
 * 		- Resume/SuspendAllInterrupts
 * 		- Enable/DisableAllInterrupts
 * 		- Resume/SuspendOSInterrupts
 * 	- GetAlarm/SetRelAlarm/SetAbsAlarm/CancelAlarm
 * 	- make depend is not yet implemented
 * 	- compilation and link is always performed from scratch
 * 	- generation is not automatic, it has to be invoked with make generate
 * 	- oil file parser is not finished.
 * 		- multi lines comments are not supported on the oil files.
 * 	- oil format may be not oil conform.
 * 	- ISR are not yet tested
 * 	- this is only a PRE BETE Release
 *
 */
